    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/savvy/d24a66d4-404e-4b87-8b81-d4e0d5248ec3/application",
    "company": "Savvy Wealth",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "66adccb2f193b67b",
    "department": "R\u0026D",
    "description": "ABOUT SAVVY WEALTH:\n\nWealth management is a $545 billion industry in the US, yet remains archaic and inefficient with low technology penetration. 75% of financial advisors don’t offer digital communication beyond email, and 62% still build financial plans manually in Excel. This leads to a poor client experience and results in financial advisors spending over 70% of their time on non-client facing, manual work.\n\nSavvy is changing that. We’re building the most advisor-centric platform in wealth management: a digital-first solution that modernizes human financial advice. Advisors who partner with Savvy tap into AI-powered software, automated sales and marketing, and seamless back office workflows to scale faster and spend more time with clients.\n\nWe’ve raised over $105M to date from Thrive Capital, Index Ventures, Canvas Ventures, Mark Casady (former LPL Financial CEO), and other top-tier investors. Our team is made up of repeat founders and operators who’ve helped build Airbnb, Square, Brex, Carta, Facebook, $200B+ RIAs, and more.\n\nSavvy is at a pivotal point in its growth trajectory, having established strong product-market fit in providing a modern platform to financial advisors. We’ve surpassed $5.1 billion in AUM in less than three years, grown 600%+ in the last 18 months, and are entering the next phase of the company which involves rapid expansion of our product offering and continued revenue growth. Come help us scale!\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Work directly with advisors and internal stakeholders to understand onboarding requirements, migrate data, and build custom solutions that accelerate their success on Savvy\n\n - Own the end-to-end product lifecycle of these initiatives from discovery and design through implementation, deployment, and iteration\n\n - Produce high-quality, maintainable, production-ready code that balances customer urgency with long-term scalability\n\n - Partner closely with Product, Design, and Operations teams to translate real customer needs into platform improvements\n\n - Debug, diagnose, and resolve live issues in collaboration with clients and internal teams\n\n - Contribute to tooling, automation, and process improvements that make future advisor migrations faster and more sustainable\n\n - Travel within the United States as needed (approximately 2-4 times per quarter) for customer migrations and collaboration sessions, typically 2 days each\n\n - Please note, we expect folks to work in office Tuesday-Thursday with the option to work from home on Mondays and Fridays\n\nMust have:\n\n - 5+ years of experience building and scaling production web applications\n\n - Strong full-stack proficiency including web frameworks (Rails preferred), front-end frameworks and libraries (React preferred), and SQL databases\n\n - Strong experience with Excel, Google Sheets, and other tools to collect and mutate data in customer-friendly formats\n\n - Proven ability to collaborate in fast-moving, cross-functional startup environments with excellent technical communication skills\n\n - Comfort working in ambiguous, customer-driven environments and balancing rapid delivery with maintainable engineering\n\nNice to have:\n\n - Experience in fintech or wealth management, especially around data migration, integrations, or advisor operations\n\n - Experience leveraging AI directly and various AI tools to translate data and integrate disparate systems, including those without APIs\n\n - Prior customer-facing engineering experience (e.g., forward-deployed, professional services, or implementation engineering)\n\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n - Competitive salary and equity package\n\n - Unlimited PTO + paid company holidays\n\n - Access to holistic medical, dental, and vision plans\n\n - Company 401(k), Commuter, and HSA/FSA plans\n\n - NYC office in the heart of Manhattan\n\n - Lunch and snacks provided in the office\n\n - Access to virtual mental health care (Spring Health), vision related benefits (XP Health), and health concierge (Rightway) to help you find the right care\n\n - Access to counseling for stress management, dependent care, nutrition, fitness, legal, and financial issues (Guardian WorkLifeMatters EAP)",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
